{% if niche.long_form %}
Write a LONG-FORM cinematic documentary video script for a crypto/finance YouTube channel.
This is a premium, Bloomberg/CNBC-style deep dive — NOT a quick news update.

Topic: {{ idea.title }}
Hook: {{ idea.hook }}
Angle: {{ idea.angle }}
Tone: {{ niche.tone }}
Target duration: {{ (niche.target_duration // 60) }}-{{ (niche.target_duration // 60) + 5 }} minutes ({{ niche.target_duration }} seconds)

{% if idea.market_data %}
Current market data (USE THESE EXACT NUMBERS — do not make up prices):
{% for coin, data in idea.market_data.items() %}
- {{ coin }}: ${{ data.usd | round(2) }}{% if data.usd_24h_change %} ({{ data.usd_24h_change | round(1) }}% 24h){% endif %}
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}

IMPORTANT CONTEXT: This video uses a MIX of real stock footage (Pexels) and AI-generated cinematic images. The voiceover narration carries the entire story — footage illustrates it. Word-by-word animated subtitles are burned in. Ambient electronic music plays underneath. This needs to be engaging enough to hold viewers for 10+ minutes — think Vice documentaries, Bloomberg Quicktake, or Vox-style explainers.

Requirements:
1. hook_text: Opening title card (first 4 seconds, max 15 words). Create IMMEDIATE curiosity or urgency.
   Examples: "The $40 Billion Crypto Scheme Nobody Saw Coming" / "Wall Street's Secret Bitcoin Play Just Leaked" / "This Chart Pattern Predicted Every Major Crash"

2. voiceover_script: Full narration, {{ (niche.target_duration // 60) * 130 }}-{{ (niche.target_duration // 60) * 170 }} words (approx 150 words per minute).

   CRITICAL WRITING GUIDELINES:
   - Open with a DRAMATIC hook: a shocking stat, a vivid scene-setting moment, or a provocative question
   - Build a clear narrative arc: Setup → Rising tension → Key insight → Implications → Conclusion
   - Include SPECIFIC data: exact dollar amounts, percentages, dates, on-chain metrics, institutional names
   - Reference real entities: BlackRock, Fidelity, SEC, Michael Saylor, CZ, Vitalik — gives credibility
   - Use rhetorical questions every 60-90 seconds to re-engage viewers: "But here's what nobody's asking..."
   - Vary pacing: fast staccato sentences for excitement, longer flowing ones for explanation
   - Include at least 2-3 "pattern interrupts" — moments that make the viewer go "wait, what?"
   - Use concrete analogies to explain complex concepts ("That's like buying every house in Manhattan — twice")
   - Each chapter transition should feel like a mini-cliffhanger
   - Write for AUDIO — every sentence should sound natural when spoken aloud
   - End with a strong, actionable takeaway — not just "subscribe"
   - Include "This is not financial advice — always do your own research before investing" woven naturally near the end

3. chapters: Array of 4-7 chapter objects for YouTube timestamp markers:
   - title: Chapter name (3-6 words). Make them intriguing, not generic.
     Good: "The Hidden Whale Signal" / "What the Charts Really Say" / "The DeFi Trap Nobody Mentions"
     Bad: "Introduction" / "Market Analysis" / "Conclusion"
   - approximate_timestamp: Estimated time in "MM:SS" format

4. scenes: Array of {{ (niche.target_duration // 60) * 2 }}-{{ (niche.target_duration // 60) * 3 }} scene objects. Each scene has:
   - search_keywords: 2-4 word Pexels search query. Be SPECIFIC and VISUAL.
     GOOD keywords for crypto/finance stock footage:
     "bitcoin cryptocurrency coins", "stock market trading screens", "wall street new york",
     "trading floor brokers", "gold bars vault", "server room technology", "city skyline night",
     "business meeting boardroom", "digital currency abstract", "cash money counting",
     "computer data analytics", "world map connections", "cryptocurrency mining farm",
     "financial newspaper headlines", "luxury lifestyle wealth", "chart graph analysis",
     "bank building exterior", "protest crowd people", "ocean waves storm",
     "clock time passing", "domino effect falling", "maze labyrinth aerial"
     AVOID: overly specific crypto terms Pexels won't have
   - image_prompt: Fallback AI image prompt. Create CINEMATIC, dramatic compositions:
     "A massive Bitcoin coin floating above a dark cityscape at night, golden glow reflecting off skyscrapers, dramatic volumetric lighting, 8K cinematic photography"
     NOT: "bitcoin image" or "crypto chart"
     Each image prompt should specify: subject, environment, lighting, camera angle, mood, color palette
   - motion_prompt: Brief description of camera motion for AI video animation (e.g. "slow dolly forward toward subject", "camera pans right across scene", "subtle zoom into center")
   - ken_burns: Fallback effect. One of: zoom_in, zoom_out, pan_left, pan_right, pan_up, pan_down. VARY across scenes.
   - duration: 15-30 seconds per scene. Total should approximately match voiceover length.
   - text_overlay: Key stat or data point (max 10 words). Use for IMPACT moments:
     "BTC: $105,000 (+12% THIS WEEK)", "WHALE ALERT: 15,000 BTC MOVED", "$2.4B LIQUIDATED IN 24 HOURS"
     Leave empty string for atmospheric/transitional scenes.
   - section: Which chapter this scene belongs to (use chapter title)

5. shorts_hooks: Array of 3-5 standalone highlights for YouTube Shorts / TikTok / Reels extraction:
   - hook_text: Punchy hook for the Short (max 12 words)
   - voiceover_excerpt: 50-70 words from the main voiceover that work as a standalone clip
   - scene_range: [start_scene_number, end_scene_number] (1-indexed) — which scenes to cut

6. captions: Platform-optimized captions:
   - youtube: 200-500 chars. Include chapter timestamps. Mention the topic and key insight.
   - tiktok: 100-150 chars. Punchy, use crypto slang. End with a question.
   - instagram: 100-200 chars. Professional but engaging.
   - facebook: 100-200 chars. Conversational, shareable.

7. hashtags: Array of 15 relevant hashtags (include: {{ niche.hashtags[:5] | join(', ') }})

8. music_tags: Array of 3-5 descriptive tags for searching SUBTLE, UNDERSTATED background music. The music must sit BEHIND the voiceover — never compete with it. Think Bloomberg/CNBC documentary underscore, not a music video. Examples: ["ambient", "electronic", "cinematic", "calm"] for market analysis, ["dark", "ambient", "atmospheric", "cinematic"] for crash/hack coverage, ["inspiring", "ambient", "cinematic", "soft"] for institutional adoption stories. AVOID tags like "energetic", "hiphop", "trap", "upbeat" — these produce distracting music that drowns out the narration.

9. music_speed: One of "verylow", "low", "medium", "high", "veryhigh" — use "low" or "medium" for most crypto content. The music should feel like a gentle pulse underneath, not a beat that demands attention.

10. thumbnail_prompt: A DRAMATIC, high-contrast thumbnail image:
   - Bold subject (giant Bitcoin, dramatic chart, shocked face)
   - Moody lighting: dark background with a single dramatic light source
   - Rich color grading: teal shadows, orange highlights (cinema LUT style)
   - NO text in the image (text is added separately)
   Example: "Extreme close-up of a golden Bitcoin coin with cracks forming on its surface, dramatic rim lighting on black background, sparks flying, cinematic color grading with deep shadows and warm gold highlights, 8K macro photography"

QUALITY STANDARDS:
- Every scene's search_keywords must be DIFFERENT — no visual repetition
- image_prompt must describe a SPECIFIC cinematic composition, not a generic concept
- text_overlay should only appear on 40-50% of scenes — visual breathing room
- The voiceover must be factually grounded — use real data, not vague claims
- Shorts excerpts must be self-contained stories that make sense without context

Return as valid JSON only. No markdown formatting, no code blocks.

